2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the distribution of personal data among several institutions and proposes a virtual entity called the Trustworthy responsible for the storage and computation of this data. This involves designing efficient data structures and algorithms for secure multiparty computation. Therefore, cs.DS is the second most likely sub-category.
3. cs.DB (Databases): The paper discusses the storage and computation of personal data by multiple institutions, which involves designing secure and efficient database systems. Therefore, cs.DB is the third most likely sub-category.
